## Rules
- Place all source code within the `src/` directory.
- Organize code into feature-based modules within `src/features/`.
  - Each feature module should contain subdirectories like `components/`, `hooks/`, `utils/`, `types.ts` as needed.
- Place shared, reusable UI components (especially Shadcn UI wrappers) in `src/components/`.
- Place shared custom hooks in `src/hooks/`.
- Place shared utility functions in `src/lib/` or `src/utils/`. Use `src/lib/utils.ts` for the `cn` function [cite: react-template-ai/src/lib/utils.ts].
- Define global types in `src/types/`.
- Store high-level AI documentation (plans, PRDs, prompts) in the `ai/` directory at the project root [cite: react-template-ai/ai/prd.md, react-template-ai/ai/plan.md, react-template-ai/ai/example-prompts.md].